RCW 47.04.200

Bicycle program manager.

The state bicycle program manager shall:(1) Design programs that encourage the use of bicycling for transportation;(2) Coordinate bicycle safety related programs and bicycle tourism programs in all state agencies;(3) Assist the department of transportation and the cities and counties of the state in assigning priorities to, programming, and developing bicycle-related projects;(4) Serve as a clearinghouse for bicycle program information and resources;(5) Provide assistance in revising and updating bicycle material of the superintendent of public instruction and the state patrol;(6) Promote the use of bicycle helmets of a type certified to meet the requirements of standard Z-90.4 of the American national standards institute or such subsequent nationally recognized standard for bicycle helmet performance; and(7) Promote bicycle safety equipment.

The state bicycle program manager shall:

(1) Design programs that encourage the use of bicycling for transportation;

(2) Coordinate bicycle safety related programs and bicycle tourism programs in all state agencies;

(3) Assist the department of transportation and the cities and counties of the state in assigning priorities to, programming, and developing bicycle-related projects;

(4) Serve as a clearinghouse for bicycle program information and resources;

(5) Provide assistance in revising and updating bicycle material of the superintendent of public instruction and the state patrol;

(6) Promote the use of bicycle helmets of a type certified to meet the requirements of standard Z-90.4 of the American national standards institute or such subsequent nationally recognized standard for bicycle helmet performance; and

(7) Promote bicycle safety equipment.

